        <body>
      
          <p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir</p>
		<p>With this you will no doubt also receive a letter <del>by</del> of <persName>M. Strauss Esq.</persName><lb/> our Parnass&#44; concerning the affairs of <persName>Mr. Henry</persName> and myself. I wrote<lb/> to you last week on the same subject&#44; but <add>&#63;</add> in the Occident<lb/> for this month that you rather somewhat disbelieve my state&#44;<lb/>ment from last year&#44; and fearing you might perhaps be induced<lb/> to do the same now&#44; I requested <persName>Mr. Strauss</persName>&#44; to write so you<lb/> on the same subject himself&#44; as the head of this congregation. I pray&#44;<lb/> do me the favour of inserting <del>the</del> his communication&#44; as your editorial<lb/> seem to have appeared just in the right time to favour <persName>Mr. Henry</persName><lb/> and so injure me. I know full well&#44; that your intention is good&#44;<lb/> and that you <sic>allways</sic> strife to do justice to all and every one with<lb/>in the influence of your <sic>correspondenze</sic> and this knowledge gives<lb/> me the hope&#8212;nay&#8212;the certainty&#44; that you will insert <persName>Mr. Strauss</persName><lb/> letter&#44; just as it reads&#44; in your next months Occident and if<lb/> you should think proper to be paid for&#44; I will cheerfully pay<lb/> myself for the insertion of the same. At the same time you<lb/> are at perfect liberty to lay by my communication on that subject&#44;<lb/> provided you will be kind enough to insert the letter of <persName>Mr. Strauss</persName>.</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)">Yours</p>
          <p rend="indent(5)">most respectfully</p>
          <p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">B H. Gotthelf</persName></p>
		<p><placeName>Louisville Ky</placeName> <date>Aug. 10<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1851</date>.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><add>Hebrew</add></p>
          
        </body>
